Apache Setup:
sudo nano /etc/apache2/apache2.conf (set root dir)
/etc/apache2/sites-available (set vhost)
/etc/letsencrypt/live/ (set ssl on vhost)
/etc/apache2/sites-enabled/(httpd.conf)(ssl.conf)
sudo ln -s /etc/apache2/sites-available/example.com.conf /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/ (enable vhost)

Forbidden Permission:
sudo chmod +x /home/user
sudo chmod +x /home/user/htdocs
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /home/user/htdocs/subdomain.domain.institute
sudo chmod -R 755 /home/user/htdocs/subdomain.domain.institute

sudo apache2ctl configtest

sudo certbot --apache -d attanal.ilannoor.institute -d www.attanal.ilannoor.institute

sudo systemctl restart apache2

tail -f /var/log/apache2/error.log

ls -l /path/to/your/php/files (ls -l command to check the permissions of the directory and files)

systemctl status apache2.service
journalctl -xeu apache2.service

Reinstalling PHP:
sudo apt-get purge apache2
sudo apt-get install apache2
sudo a2enmod rewrite
sudo service apache2 stop
sudo service apache2 start
